        <abstract>
            <p>Has reported on the Naples Zoological Station to BAAS meeting at Brighton. Hopes to open it in January. Is at work building up the library by contributions from publishers and naturalists.</p>
            <p>Deplores Wallace’s "drifting away" and his association with such men as H. C. Bastian.</p>
            <p>Disbelieves in ascidians as our ancestors. Has a substitute he is sure will please CD.</p>
        </abstract>
